procedures.name: Blood Sampling

code.decode: Collection of venous blood by venipuncture

procedures.label: Blood Draw
procedures.description: Collection of blood samples for pharmacokinetic (PK), pharmacodynamic (PD), and clinical safety laboratory assessments (serum chemistry, hematology, coagulation).

procedures.name: Urine Collection
procedures.label: Urine Sample Collection
procedures.description: Collection of urine for urinalysis, drug screen, pregnancy tests, and measurement of copper and molybdenum content.

procedures.name: 24-hour Urine Collection
procedures.label: 24h Urine Collection
procedures.description: 24-hour urine samples are collected for measurement of copper and molybdenum.

procedures.name: Fecal Collection
procedures.label: Stool Sample Collection
procedures.description: Collection of fecal samples for measurement of copper and molybdenum content.

procedures.name: Physical Examination
procedures.label: Physical Exam
procedures.description: A full physical examination including assessments of the cardiovascular, respiratory, gastrointestinal, and neurological systems.

procedures.name: Vital Signs Measurement
procedures.label: Vital Signs
procedures.description: Assessment of body temperature, heart rate, respiratory rate, and systolic and diastolic blood pressure.

procedures.name: 12-lead Electrocardiogram

code.decode: Electrocardiogram, routine ECG with at least 12 leads; with interpretation and report

procedures.label: ECG
procedures.description: Triplicate 12-lead ECG to assess heart rate, intervals (PR, QRS, QT and QTc), and clinically significant findings.

procedures.name: Oral Administration of Study Intervention
procedures.label: Drug Administration
procedures.description: Participants swallow intact ALXN1840 tablets with 240 mL of water after an overnight fast.

procedures.name: Clinical Safety Laboratory Assessments
procedures.label: Safety Labs
procedures.description: Includes serum chemistry, hematology, coagulation, and urinalysis.

procedures.name: Pregnancy Test
procedures.label: Pregnancy Test
procedures.description: Urine or serum pregnancy tests for women of childbearing potential.

procedures.name: Urine Drug Screen
procedures.label: Urine Drug Screen
procedures.description: Screening for drugs of abuse via urine sample.

procedures.name: HIV, Hepatitis B and C Screen

code.decode: HIV, Hepatitis B and C Screen

procedures.label: Viral Screen
procedures.description: Blood test to screen for Human Immunodeficiency Virus, Hepatitis B, and Hepatitis C.

procedures.name: Height, Weight, and BMI Measurement
procedures.label: Anthropometrics
procedures.description: Measurement of height, weight, and calculation of Body Mass Index (BMI).

procedures.name: Adverse Event Monitoring
procedures.label: AE Monitoring
procedures.description: Ongoing monitoring and collection of adverse event (AE) and serious adverse event (SAE) information.

procedures.name: Cannula Placement
procedures.label: Cannulation
procedures.description: A cannula may be placed to minimize needle sticks for repeated blood draws.

procedures.name: Food and Fluid Sample Collection
procedures.label: Dietary Sample Collection
procedures.description: Samples of all meal and fluid batches will be collected and analyzed for measurement of copper and molybdenum content.

medicalDevices.name: 12-lead ECG Device
medicalDevices.label: ECG Machine
medicalDevices.description: Device used to perform triplicate 12-lead electrocardiograms.

medicalDevices.name: Automated Blood Pressure Device
medicalDevices.label: Automated BP Monitor
medicalDevices.description: A completely automated device for assessing blood pressure and heart rate measurements.

medicalDevices.name: Cannula
medicalDevices.label: Cannula
medicalDevices.description: A cannula may be placed to minimize needle sticks for repeated blood draws.

medicalDevices.name: Catheter
medicalDevices.label: Catheter
medicalDevices.description: A catheter may be used for venous access but not left in place for longer than 72 hours.

medicalDevices.name: Inductively Coupled Plasma Mass Spectrometry
medicalDevices.label: ICP-MS
medicalDevices.description: Device used to determine the copper and molybdenum concentration of food, fluid, urine, and fecal samples.
